The Chief Judge of Kogi State, Justice Nasiru Ajanah has sworn-in 21 court judges in the state. The new court judges comprise 9 Magistrates and 12 Senior Area court judges. Justice Nasiru Ajanah while swearing in the judges on Monday at the State High Court in Lokoja, charged them to abreast themselves with the new developments in law to enable them to keep their decisions and judgements spiced with up to date legal knowledge. He said that the administration of a Justice needs lower court judges that are proactive and diligent in their duties, urging them to “watch the case flow in their court and ensure they have a return on cases that are commendable” While advising the newly inaugurated lower court judges to exhibit courage, patience, knowledge, wisdom, and integrity as qualities and virtues that would propel them to discharge their duties creditably, Justice Ajanah told the Magistrates and Area Court Judges that the Kogi State Judiciary has zero-tolerance for corruption, saying “your integrity is your number one asset in this task and you must be above board”. ALSO READ: UNILAG produces 281 First class as 51st convocation holds, launches anthem He reminded them that “You all went through a rigorous process of selection at the Judicial Service Commission before your appointment. “Your appointment is prima facie evidence of your competence and ability. However, when you begin to sit as Magistrates and Area Court Judges you will need to justify the confidence reposed on you by this appointment. “While I congratulate the families and friends that have come to share this day of joy with them; I must warn that you allow the new Magistrates and Area Court Judges to do their jobs without pressuring them to flout their judicial oath. “The best you can do for them from this day is to pray that God will grant them the courage to take judicial decisions without fear or favour” he warned. The newly appointed Magistrates are Usman Muhammed Enesi, Khadijat Kassim, Ugbedeojo A. Susan, Ajibola Olushola Sunday, Abdullahi Illiyasu, Ogido Hannah Ize, Tosin Shalom Orunmbe, Olushola Bamidele Seun and David Ojomah. While the Area Court Judges are Abubakar Dauda, Isah Nimmah Ozavize, Ogunlaiye O. Emmanuel, Owonibi Iyabode Olayemi, Ibrahim B. Abdulkarim, Fadamijo Daniel Praise. Others are Shuaibu Abdulganiyu, Isah Shifao Oyiza, Mohammed N. Abubakar, Edini Daniel, Suleiman Mohammed Ada and Ahmed Khadijat O. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! HERE IS HOW OVER 5000  NIGERIA MEN HAVE PERMANENTLY OVERCOME TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS RECENT DISCOVERY BY MEDICAL CONSULTANTS LOOK!  YOU DONT NEED TO HAVE ANY EXPERIENCE TO TRADE ONLINE,WE WILL DO IT ALL FOR YOU AND YOU WILL START EARNING A LIVING FROM TRADING ONLINE TODAY AND PROFITS WILL BE PAID TO YOUR ACCOUNT DIRECTLY. CLICK HERE TO REGISTER AND EARN